questiontext.text:
A survey with 50 persons was conducted to analyze the design of an advertising campaign. Each respondent was asked to evaluate the overall impression of the advertisement on an eleven-point scale from 0 (bad) to 10 (good). The evaluations are summarized separately with respect to type of occupation of the respondents in the following figure.

To analyze the influence of occupation on the evaluation of the advertisement an analysis of variance was performed:

  Res.Df    RSS Df Sum of Sq     F    Pr(>F)
1     49 42.177                             
2     46 26.979  3    15.198 8.638 0.0001177

Which of the following statements are correct?

generalfeedback.text:
In order to be able to answer the questions the fraction of explained variance has to be determined. The residual sum of squares when using only a single overall mean value (\(\mathit{RSS}_0\)) as well as the residual sum of squares when allowing different mean values given occupation (\(\mathit{RSS}_1\)) are required. Both are given in the RSS column of the ANOVA table. The fraction of explained variance is given by \(1 - \mathit{RSS}_1/\mathit{RSS}_0 = 1 - 26.979/42.177 = 0.36\).

The statements above can now be evaluated as right or wrong.

  1. False. The test statistic is \(F = 8.638\) and hence not larger than \(23.6\).
  2. True. The \(p\) value is \(0.000118\) and hence significant. It can be shown that the evaluations differ with respect to the occupation of the respondents.
  3. True. The fraction of explained variance is \(0.360\) and hence larger than 0.3.
  4. False. An ANOVA always tests the null hypothesis, that all mean values are equal against the alternative hypothesis that they are different.
  5. False. The fraction of explained variance is \(0.360\) and hence not smaller than 0.25.

answer.text: The test statistic is larger than \(23.6\).

feedback.text: False. The test statistic is \(F = 8.638\) and hence not larger than \(23.6\).

answer.text: It can be shown that the evaluation of the respondents depends on their occupation. (Significance level \(5\)%)

feedback.text: True. The \(p\) value is \(0.000118\) and hence significant. It can be shown that the evaluations differ with respect to the occupation of the respondents.

answer.text: The fraction of explained variance is larger than \(30\)%.

feedback.text: True. The fraction of explained variance is \(0.360\) and hence larger than 0.3.

answer.text: A one-sided alternative was tested for the mean values.

feedback.text: False. An ANOVA always tests the null hypothesis, that all mean values are equal against the alternative hypothesis that they are different.

answer.text: The fraction of explained variance is smaller than \(25\)%.

feedback.text: False. The fraction of explained variance is \(0.360\) and hence not smaller than 0.25.
